  "description": "The Liebherr brand’s two-chamber refrigerator can be categorized as an advanced-class solution, while being one of the entry-level units within the brand's lineup. The model features a relatively compact body width of <b>55 cm</b>, making it an appealing choice for small kitchens or other limited living spaces. The Liebherr CUele 3331 refrigerator is <b>181 cm</b> tall and offers a total volume of <b>296 liters</b>, making it primarily recommended for small to medium families. The <b>84-liter</b> freezer compartment, located at the bottom, includes 3 pull-out transparent drawers. It can freeze approximately 4 kg of food <b>per day</b> and maintain cold for up to 16 hours without electricity. The <b>212-liter</b> refrigerator section features four open storage areas, a bottle holder (designed for <b>5 bottles</b>), two vegetable boxes, and four wide door pockets. Note that the model has a <b>single cooling circuit</b>, meaning there is no independent temperature control in the two chambers. The operating mode can only be adjusted in the refrigeration section using a rotary switch. The freezer requires manual defrosting, but the <b>SmartFrost</b> technology helps reduce ice build-up, thus requiring less maintenance from users. Highlights include its moderate noise level (up to <b>40 dB</b>), energy consumption rated at class E with an annual consumption of <b>224 kWh</b>, and operation with the eco-friendly refrigerant <b>R 600a</b>.",
